DocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104jsq1665702796206.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jsq1665702796206.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/jsq1665702796206.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"jsq1665702796206\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Application Shell Editor\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Use the Application Shell Editor to define the main executable component for a desktop application or Uniface Server.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jsq1665702796206__section_w0ab1b7b1_w1ab1b7_w2ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\"></p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jsq1665702796206__section_w3ab1b7b3_w4ab1b7_w5ab1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ohj1705472401504.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ohj1705472401504.html\" title=\"An application shell is a module used to initialize and run an application (Windows or character-based) or application server.\">Application Shells</a>.</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"jsq1665702796206__section_w6ab1b7b5_w7ab1b7_w8ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d937639e70\">\n                       \n How to\n </h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jsq1665702796206__li_d2687e1_d2688e1_d2689e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"tzk1705564326555.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tzk1705564326555.html\" title=\"An application shell is required to run Windows and character-based applications.\">Define an Application Shell</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jsq1665702796206__li_d2690e1_d2691e1_d2692e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qle1665702773192.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qle1665702773192.html\" title=\"Use the Uniface IDE to develop an application, following the Uniface development paradigm of Model, Construct, Build, and Deploy.\">Using the Uniface IDE</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"jsq1665702796206__li_d2693e1_d2694e1_d2695e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dkp1665702773261.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dkp1665702773261.html\" title=\"Although development objects can be quite different in content and purpose, the way you create, edit and delete them in the Uniface IDE is essentially the same.\">Working with Development Objects</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"p\">\n<figure class=\"fig fignone\" id=\"jsq1665702796206__fig_w9ab1b7b5b7b1_w10ab1b7b5b7_w11ab1b7b5_w12ab1b7_w13ab1\"><figcaption><span class=\"fig--title-label\">Figure 1. </span>Application Shell Editor for Windows Application </figcaption>\n<img alt=\"Application Shell Editor for Windows Application\" class=\"image\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/apseditor_win.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529028\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529028\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Application Shell Editor Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Application Shell Editor Use the Application Shell Editor to define the main executable component for a desktop application or Uniface Server. For more information, see Application Shells . How to Define an Application Shell Using the Uniface IDE Working with Development Objects Figure 1. Application Shell Editor for Windows Application Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}